The grid parameter must be a 2-dimensional array of integers.
The grid must not be null.
The grid must have at least one row and one column.
Each element in the grid must be a non-negative integer.
The grid represents a mine where each cell contains a certain amount of gold.
The player can start at any cell in the grid.
The player can only move up, down, left, or right to adjacent cells.
The player cannot move diagonally or move to cells outside the grid.
The player can only visit each cell once.
The player can collect the gold in the cell they are currently in.
The player can only move to a cell with gold if they have not collected gold from that cell before.
The player can only move to a cell without gold if they have already collected gold from all adjacent cells.
The player can collect gold from multiple cells in a single path.
The player's goal is to collect the maximum amount of gold possible.
The method should return an integer representing the maximum amount of gold that can be collected.